{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TfnF84n42LkxqRxRDjkoBz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_012qCQRRTiVtHNPUkb4sPf7g","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/aparkin/BERIL-research-observatory/projects/caulobacter_fur_lipida_loss/talks/draft_1/audit/revisions/F006.revised_slide.json","content":"{\n  \"id\": 17,\n  \"position\": 17,\n  \"substory_id\": \"S3\",\n  \"layout\": \"data_figure\",\n  \"content\": {\n    \"title\": \"Lpt apparatus maintained at transcript; LptD/LptE protein decline reveals Layer 3 tension\",\n    \"figure\": \"figures/NB04_lpt_apparatus_heatmap.png\",\n    \"caption\": \"Canonical Lpt CPM heatmap: MsbA-like CCNA_00307 UP (+0.89, FDR 0.01) and LptC-related CCNA_03716 UP (+0.56, FDR 0.005) at transcript; LptD protein −0.47 and LptE −0.78 against transcript. Single-replicate OM proteome; discordance unresolved.\",\n    \"data_source\": \"REPORT.md §Finding 4; NB04_sphingolipid_lpt_panel.ipynb cells 3,5,6\"\n  },\n  \"speaker_notes_seed\": \"The NB04_lpt_apparatus_heatmap shows CPM (log2) for canonical Lpt components across the strain series. The visual story is asymmetric: MsbA-like CCNA_00307 (+0.89 transcript, FDR 0.01) and LptC-related CCNA_03716 (+0.56, FDR 0.005) are the upward outliers in the rescued strain — consistent with Uchendu 2026’s shared-component model for inner-membrane sphingolipid transport. No canonical Lpt component is significantly down at transcript level.\\n\\nThe tension lives in the single-replicate OM proteome (REPORT §Finding 4 protein table): LptD (CCNA_01760) log2(4672/4659) = −0.47 and LptE (CCNA_03866) = −0.78 — both decline at protein level despite stable/up transcripts. A parsimonious interpretation: with no LPS substrate, canonical LPS-specific Lpt machinery may be less occupied or actively turned over. But single-replicate proteomics cannot discriminate substrate-limitation from active downregulation; the verdict is DISCORDANT, not PASS.\\n\\nPilot signals not shown in the figure (speaker background): lptC2 (CCNA_01226) transcript −0.60 FDR 0.034, protein log2(4672/4659) = +1.08 vs intermediate (+0.66 vs WT baseline after accounting for prior −0.42 step) — labeled PILOT, requires replication. CCNA_01217 protein +0.77 vs intermediate, +0.74 vs WT — a second directional pilot datum. CtpA (CCNA_03113) REJECTED at pre-registered bar: FDR 0.109 (fails lower bound of 0.05), protein not detected in OM proteome.\",\n  \"evidence_anchors\": [\n    {\"kind\": \"report_section\", \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §Finding 4\"},\n    {\"kind\": \"report_section\", \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §NB04 image caption\"}\n  ],\n  \"revision_log\": [\n    {\n      \"revised_at\": \"2026-06-07T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"finding_id\": \"F006\",\n      \"finding_class\": \"substory_arc\",\n      \"summary\": \"Converted layout from data_table to data_figure using NB04_lpt_apparatus_heatmap.png; title and caption reframed around A14/A15 (Lpt transcript maintained/up vs LptD/LptE protein discordance); pilot data (lptC2/CCNA_01217 PILOTs, CtpA REJECTED) moved to speaker_notes_seed; restores S3 substory plan’s data_figure slot for A14/A15 as specified in 02_substories.md.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6804,"cache_read_input_tokens":42340,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6804},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ba2d6b0f-241e-4c07-96a3-a6effebadbb7","uuid":"57c44b69-3dc5-44a7-88e7-a514e60db6cb"}
